      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: THE BOEING COMPANY (BA)\n\n**Date of Signal: May 6, 2026 | Amount: $22.4B | Action: BUY**\n\n---\n\nBoeing received two NASA contracts totaling over $32.9 billion combined at a moment when the company faces active federal oversight investigations, congressional scrutiny over its safety certification processes, and documented regulatory failures tied to the 737 MAX and 787 programs — raising direct questions about whether contract awards reflect competitive merit or sustained political relationships. Boeing has contributed millions to members of the Senate Commerce Committee and House Appropriations subcommittees that oversee both NASA funding and aerospace procurement, with lawmakers receiving Boeing PAC money subsequently voting to authorize or expand the agency's commercial crew and Space Launch System budget lines. The SLS program, a primary vehicle for Boeing's NASA revenue, has been publicly documented by the Government Accountability Office as running **years behind schedule and billions over budget**, yet contract awards have continued without competitive rebidding. This pattern mirrors Boeing's documented history with the KC-46 tanker program, where cost overruns exceeding $7 billion were absorbed by the Pentagon while the contract remained intact — a structural dynamic that has repeated across three consecutive administrations.\n\n---\n\n**⚠️ NOTE:** The \"$22.4B buy signal\" referenced here is an **algorithmic trading signal**, not a disclosed congressional trade. Readers should distinguish between market signals and verified insider activity. Verification of beneficial ownership and disclosure filings is recommended before drawing legal conclusions.\n\n*Sources cross-reference: GAO, FEC, USASpending.gov, ProPublica Nonprofit Explorer*"
